article.headline: Western Michigan downs Tennessee State 63-52
article.story: HONOLULU -- Shayne Whittington led Western Michigan with a double-double to close out the Rainbow Classic with a 63-52 win over Tennessee State Monday. Whittington, who scored 14 points and pulled down 12 rebounds, was one of four Broncos in double figures as Western Michigan (2-1) never trailed. David Brown had 17 points, Connar Tava contributed 16 and Austin Richie had 11. Patrick Miller led Tennessee State (0-3) with 17 points. M.J. Rhett had 10 points and 9 rebounds. Western Michigan had defeated New Mexico State 70-64 and lost to Hawaii 78-68 earlier in Classic games. The Broncos opened with a 7-0 run and never looked back, sprinting to a 31-21 halftime advantage. The second half was tighter as Western Michigan won that period 32-31. Both teams had 37 rebounds for the game, but Western Michigan put away 17 of 20 free throws and hit 38 percent from the floor.
